            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "A potential problem here is that it may be hard to tell a normal server exit using `:cquit` from a server crash. If the server exits using `:cquit` the client should just exit with the same exit code to keep backward-compatibility.\r\n\r\nA possible solution is to add a \"stop\" UI event and make the server send it when exiting normally, so when the server exits without sending a \"stop\" event it has likely crashed.",
